All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Area
The various instances of area …
AreaValue
A value class for areas.
AreaValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for AreaValue instances.
DataSize
The various instances of data sizes (for files or free disk space or capacities of memory sticks …).
DataSizeValue
A value class for byte values, as for file sizes, disk capacities or alike.
DataSizeValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for DataSizeValue instances.
Dimension
The implementations of this interface are used to give (numerical) values a dimension and a measuring unit.
DimensionedValue<D extends Dimension>
The definition for a value with a dimension.
DimensionedValueStringConverter<D extends Dimension,V extends DimensionedValue<D>>
The abstract base class for implementations of StringConverter for dimensioned values.
Length
The various instances of length …
LengthValue
A value class for lengths.
LengthValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for LengthValue instances.
Mass
The various instances of masses and weights (although this is not really the same, from a physical or scientific point of view ...).
MassValue
A value class for weights and masses.
MassValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for MassValue instances.
Pressure
The various instances of pressure.
PressureValue
A value class for pressure values.
PressureValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for PressureValue instances.
Speed
The various instances of speed …
SpeedValue
A value class for speeds.
SpeedValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for SpeedValue instances.
Time
The various instances of time periods …
TimeValue
A value class for times, what means periods of time in this case, opposite to the time displayed on the wall-clock.
TimeValueStringConverter
The implementation of StringConverter for TimeValue instances.
ValueBase<D extends Dimension,I extends DimensionedValue<D>>
An abstract base implementation for the interface DimensionedValue that is intended as the base for concrete implementations of value types.
